Definition:
Computer networking refers to the interconnection of multiple devices to share data and resources.

Types of Networks:
- LAN (Local Area Network)
- WAN (Wide Area Network)
- MAN (Metropolitan Area Network)

Network Devices:
- Router
- Switch
- Hub
- Modem

Benefits:
- File sharing
- Internet access
- Centralized data storage
